We are wiring our swerveMAX base and checking to make sure everything works however we ran into a problem with our front right turning motor controller where on the REV hardware client it is displaying that it is receiving 20 volts when it should be receiving 12 as it is wired directly through CAN as well as the REV Power Distribution Hub (displaying 12.6ish volts) Every single other motor controller in our swerve base is properly reading and receiving 12 volts
In the driver station we are getting the CAN error 4: WPILib or External HAL Error: CAN: Message not found Periodic Status 5

Here are the things we have tried:

  1. checking all wiring directly to the controller
  2. replacing the controller for a new one (making sure everything is programmed correctly on the new controller)
  3. switching the port in the PDH
  4. Skimmed through code to check for obvious faults
    After these attempts it is still reading around 20 volts
